It&#8217;s understood a group attacked a local family&#8217;s homestead in the Madulini area late on Saturday night. JOHANNESBURG Police in KwaZulu-Natal (KZN) have arrested five men who allegedly burnt their neighbours to death following an argument.It s understood the group attacked a local family's homestead in the Madulini area in northern KwaZulu-Natal late on Saturday night.The police s Thulane Zwane says the victims were severely assaulted before being set alight. It s alleged that on 29 October the victims were in their house when they were attacked by these five suspects. The two were badly assaulted and were set [alight] while in the hut. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)